The probability of rolling a 1 is 1/E, the probability of rolling a 2 is 2/E, the probability of rolling a 3 is 3/E, the probability of rolling a 4 is 4/E, the probability of rolling a 5 is 5/E, and the probability of rolling a 6 is 6/E.  Therefore, 
\begin{align*}
E&=1\left(\frac{1}{E}\right)+2\left(\frac{2}{E}\right)+3\left(\frac{3}{E}\right)+4\left(\frac{4}{E}\right)+5\left(\frac{5}{E}\right)+6\left(\frac{6}{E}\right)\\
&=\frac{1+4+9+16+25+36}{E}\\
&=\frac{91}{E}
\end{align*}

